Wardyń Górny  (German Hohenwardin) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Połczyn-Zdrój, within Świdwin County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  west of Połczyn-Zdrój,  east of Świdwin, and  north-east of the regional capital Szczecin.
